BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 546.0 Tm (### 4.1 Maze Layout) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 522.0 Tm (The environment is defined on a 20x20 grid. Each cell is either:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 498.0 Tm (- a wall) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 483.0 Tm (- an empty traversable space) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 468.0 Tm (- a pellet location) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 444.0 Tm (Pacman and the ghost occupy valid open cells. At reset, pellets are placed in all) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 429.0 Tm (traversable cells except the current spawn positions.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 405.0 Tm (### 4.2 Episode Start) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 381.0 Tm (The environment supports two reset modes:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 357.0 Tm (- deterministic start positions for evaluation and visualization) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 342.0 Tm (- randomized start positions for training) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 318.0 Tm (Randomized starts were added to prevent route memorization. Pacman and the ghost are also) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 303.0 Tm (forced to begin a minimum maze distance apart during training so the agent has time to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 288.0 Tm (explore meaningfully.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 264.0 Tm (### 4.3 Action Space) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 240.0 Tm (Pacman has four discrete actions:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 216.0 Tm (- up) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 201.0 Tm (- down) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 186.0 Tm (- left) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 171.0 Tm (- right) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 147.0 Tm (Illegal actions that would move into walls are masked during action selection.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 123.0 Tm (### 4.4 Ghost Behavior) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 99.0 Tm (The ghost is rule-based rather than learned. It computes a shortest path toward Pacman and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 84.0 Tm (takes the first step on that path. This makes the ghost deterministic, interpretable, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 69.0 Tm (consistent.) Tj ET
endstream
