BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 738 Tm (Legal-action masking prevents the network from choosing wall collisions as valid decisions.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 714.0 Tm (8. Training Pipeline) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 684.0 Tm (### 8.1 Experience Replay) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 660.0 Tm (Training uses a replay buffer that stores transitions:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 636.0 Tm (- state) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 621.0 Tm (- action) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 606.0 Tm (- reward) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 591.0 Tm (- next state) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 576.0 Tm (- done flag) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 561.0 Tm (- mask of legal next actions) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 537.0 Tm (Replay reduces temporal correlation between consecutive samples and improves sample) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 522.0 Tm (efficiency.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 498.0 Tm (### 8.2 Target Network) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 474.0 Tm (A separate target network is used for bootstrap targets. This stabilizes learning by) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 459.0 Tm (preventing the network from chasing its own rapidly changing estimates at every step.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 435.0 Tm (### 8.3 Double DQN Update) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 411.0 Tm (The project uses a Double DQN style target:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 387.0 Tm (- the online network selects the best next action) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 372.0 Tm (- the target network evaluates that action) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 348.0 Tm (This reduces overestimation bias compared with naive max-Q targets.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 324.0 Tm (### 8.4 Loss Function) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 300.0 Tm (Training uses Huber loss, which is less sensitive to large outliers than mean squared error) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 285.0 Tm (and is often more stable for Q-learning.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 261.0 Tm (### 8.5 Reward Clipping for Training) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 237.0 Tm (To improve stability, training stores clipped rewards in replay even though the environment) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 222.0 Tm (logs the original rewards. This preserves interpretability in the logs while preventing) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 207.0 Tm (large reward magnitudes from destabilizing value estimation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 183.0 Tm (### 8.6 Curriculum Learning) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 159.0 Tm (Curriculum learning was introduced after early experiments showed that Pacman was learning) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 144.0 Tm (only short pellet-harvesting routes before dying.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 120.0 Tm (The curriculum makes training easier in the beginning by:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 96.0 Tm (- slowing ghost movement further than the final target speed) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 81.0 Tm (- delaying ghost activation) Tj ET
endstream
