BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 645.0 Tm (Several practical challenges emerged during development:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 621.0 Tm (### 10.1 Local Optima) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 597.0 Tm (Pacman often learned to collect a moderate number of pellets and then accept death, because) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 582.0 Tm (that policy produced higher short-term return than exploring a riskier long route.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 558.0 Tm (### 10.2 Oscillation) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 534.0 Tm (The agent sometimes learned to move back and forth in safe corners. This was mitigated with) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 519.0 Tm (small anti-loop penalties and improved curriculum design.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 495.0 Tm (### 10.3 Deterministic Memorization) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 471.0 Tm (Fixed start states made it easy for Pacman to memorize narrow opening sequences. Randomized) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 456.0 Tm (starts reduced this issue.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 432.0 Tm (### 10.4 Instability in Deep Q-Learning) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 408.0 Tm (Large reward magnitudes and bootstrapped targets can create unstable training. Reward) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 393.0 Tm (clipping, target networks, and Huber loss improved this significantly.) Tj ET
