BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 660.0 Tm (- reason over corridors and bottlenecks) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 645.0 Tm (- choose between safe and risky routes) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 621.0 Tm (This is conceptually very similar to Pacman collecting pellets while avoiding the ghost.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 597.0 Tm (### 12.2 Autonomous Vehicles) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 573.0 Tm (Autonomous systems must continuously trade off:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 549.0 Tm (- progress toward a goal) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 534.0 Tm (- safety around dynamic hazards) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 519.0 Tm (- path efficiency) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 504.0 Tm (- local versus long-term outcomes) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 480.0 Tm (The Pacman task is a simplified version of this decision structure.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 456.0 Tm (### 12.3 Supply Chain and Routing) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 432.0 Tm (Route planning under uncertainty often involves maximizing pickups or deliveries while) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 417.0 Tm (minimizing exposure to congestion, delays, or failures. The same structure appears in) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 402.0 Tm (Pacman:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 378.0 Tm (- collect rewards efficiently) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 363.0 Tm (- avoid costly interactions) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 348.0 Tm (- use the map intelligently) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 324.0 Tm (### 12.4 Cybersecurity) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 300.0 Tm (Automated defense systems often need to:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 276.0 Tm (- gather information) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 261.0 Tm (- preserve system availability) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 246.0 Tm (- avoid high-risk actions) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 231.0 Tm (- react to adversarial behavior) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 207.0 Tm (This project reflects the same kind of strategic balance between progress and avoidance.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 183.0 Tm (### 12.5 Resource-Constrained Planning) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 159.0 Tm (Many business and engineering problems require optimizing under threat or uncertainty rather) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 144.0 Tm (than simply maximizing raw gain. PacManDRL serves as a compact demonstration of this broader) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 129.0 Tm (RL principle.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 105.0 Tm (13. Skills Demonstrated by the Project) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 75.0 Tm (This project demonstrates strong practical ability in:) Tj ET
